The community of Meadowlands in Soweto is holding a candlelight memorial in honour of Tshegofatso Pule. The pregnant 28-year-old was found hanging from a tree in Johannesburg. Courtesy #DStv403 Manqoba Mchunu is there. JOHANNESBURG - The community of Meadowlands in Soweto is holding a candlelight memorial in honour of Tshegofatso Pule, who was found murdered this week. The 28-year-old was 8 months pregnant at the time of her death. She was found hanging from a tree in Johannesburg. The community of Meadowlands in Soweto is united in pain. This afternoon community members are holding candlelight memorial in honour of a young woman who was murdered this week. Courtesy #DStv403 Family friend, Ntombi Zwane, says she is still in disbelief following the news of Pule's death. "It is very sad what has happened to Tshego, you know when I heard the news on Monday morning, I was very shocked. READ: Tshegofatso Pule to be laid to rest on Thursday "She was 8 months pregnant. We were hoping to have a baby shower and she was due to give birth on the first week of July. She was brutally killed, I don't know who would do such a cruel thing," she said. Pule will be laid to rest on Thursday. There's more outrage among South Africans following the latest murders of women. 28-year-old Tshegofatso Pule was found hanging from a tree in the Roodepoort area on Monday, after being reported missing on the 4th of June. She was 8 months pregnant. Courtesy #DStv403